text: Bastian Kaltenböck (born July 23, 1983 in Hallein, Austria) is a ski jumper from Austria. Kaltenböck competed in the Ski jumping World Cup between 2003 and 2009. He also has nine individual Continental Cup-wins. In the 2010 Winter Olympics Kaltenböck ended his career as a trialjumper.
